the 1977 montreal alouettes finished the season in 1st place in the east division with an 11–5–0 record and won the grey cup. the alouettes set cfl attendance records for the most attended regular season game with 69,093 fans attending the september 6 match-up with the toronto argonauts and for the most attended grey cup game with 68,205 people attending the 65th grey cup. both records still stand today.